data.description: Camden Property Trust is a real estate investment trust, which engages in the provision of ownership, management, development, reposition, redevelopment, acquisition, and construction of multifamily apartment communities. The company is headquartered in Houston, Texas and currently employs 1,660 full-time employees.  The firm and its subsidiaries are primarily engaged in the ownership, management, development, reposition, redevelopment, acquisition, and construction of multifamily apartment communities. The company owns and operates approximately 175 properties containing over 59,210 apartment homes across the United States. The company also has four properties under development. Its properties typically consist of mid-rise buildings or two-and three-story buildings in a landscaped setting, as well as high-rise buildings, and provide residents with a variety of amenities common to multifamily rental properties. The firm's properties include Camden Chandler, Camden Copper Square, Camden Foothills, Camden Legacy, Camden Glendale, Camden Landmark, Camden Flatirons, Camden Ashburn Farm and others. Its properties are located in Arizona, California, Colorado, Washington District of Columbia (DC) Metro, Florida and others.
